title: Gorman fullback gets his due in homecoming win against Durango - High School Sports News -
text:
More Coverage Friday Night Roundup: Find out if your team won this week http://lasvegassun.com/news/2015/oct/08/once-a-gator-always-a-gator-henderson-bowl-rivalry/ High School Football Picks: Week 7 The Sun's high school football section The Bishop Gorman High football team’s fullback Alec Lazarou usually doesn’t receive many carries. Rather, he typically blocks for the defending mythical national champion’s stable of college-caliber running backs.
Today, during Gorman’s homecoming game against Durango, Lazarou got a rare carry close to the endzone. He responded with a 1-yard touchdown run, helping the Gaels finish off Durango 69-7.
“He’s been blocking for these guys for three years,” Gorman coach Kenny Sanchez said. “Glad we finally got him his first touchdown.”
Biaggo Ali-Walsh, Gorman’s dynamic junior running back, rushed for two touchdowns and 102 yards on just two carries. Quarterback Tate Martell passed for three touchdowns — two to Brandon Gahagan — before giving way to the second team, including senior Troy Wilewski, who rushed for a touchdown.
